09/01/2007
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- A meeting between the island's Greek Orthodox Archbishop Chrysostomos and Muslim religious community head Ahmet Yonluer, due to take place on Monday (January 8th), was called off that morning by Yonluer.
He that the "climate is not favourable" and that the archbishop's preliminary remarks suggested an attempt to politicise the agenda.
This would have been the first such meeting in decades.
(Kathimerini - 09/01/07;
CNA, Zaman, Anadolu Agency - 08/01/07)
